Usually, I find myself a step or two behind, but through Kindle, I found that I was moving at such a slow pace (or Adriene was in overdrive through out).  I was in a good place throughout but I just kept on thinking that I was falling further and further behind but I didn't give up and switch off, I continued and as always after the session, I feel as though this journey is benefiting me in some way.

I am having such a hard time with my wellbeing that I am just looking for ways to calm down and relax and I find when I am going through these motions, I am feel as though I am in a good place. Wow. Today during the second round of the tree pose (on our right foot), I found myself in tears. In reflection on the why, I think it's because - (1) my counselor/therapist explained at the end of last week that she wanted me to re-take the myers briggs personality test, as she thought that when I initially took it three years ago that I had answered the questions based on who I thought I should be rather than on who I truly am. I re-took the test this weekend, and indeed my results came out differently. Today at the start of our practice I cheered on my mat to resting in and being who I TRUEly am. (2) I broke my right foot in July and have been working on recovering ever since, and have really been struggling to balance on that (my right) foot. My LAST physical therapy appointment is finally* tomorrow. Today during the tree pose, I really struggled on the left foot (in the first round of the pose) so when we switched to the right foot... I felt a twinge of doubt, knowing I'd struggle on my right foot even more, but trying to just be okay with it. I ended up being BETTER on my right foot! And then we were led to express ourselves - I lifted my hands to the air in praise, and felt the unexpected tears begin. It was really really neat. Thank you so much, Adriene. - Ashlee Schmitt *
